This paper deals with the mathematical modeling of equilibrium solutions in Arrow-Debreu markets, which is a topic in game theory and microeconomics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also involves convex optimization and linear programming, which are topics in computer science, hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the existence and rationality of equilibria, which is a topic in economics, hence cs.EC (Economics) is another likely category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical proofs and optimization techniques, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category.
